{
  "text": "The cells were incubated with LysoTracker Red DND-99 (75 nM), which is an acidic pH marker for lysosomes, for 30 min to visualize lysosomes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The co-localization of GFP-LC3 punctae and LysoTracker was examined with the Operetta highthroughput optical imager and analyzed with the integrated Columbus image data storage and analysis system. The rate of autophagosome-lysosome fusion was calculated as the percentage of autolysosomes relative to autophagosomes.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "19040202",
